headline: Is Record 2025 Results and Cautious 2026 Outlook Altering The Investment Case For Intuitive Surgical (ISRG)?
summary: Intuitive Surgical, Inc. has reported past fourth-quarter 2025 revenue of US$2.87 billion and full-year revenue of US$10.06 billion, alongside higher net income and earnings per share compared with 2024. The company’s strong growth in procedures across its da Vinci and Ion platforms, coupled with cautious 2026 procedure guidance, is sharpening investor focus on how rising competition and utilization trends could influence its longer-term positioning in robotic surgery.
